== Description ==
[[File:Stringrayvideo.mp4|thumb|240x240px|A found desktop recording of The Stingray. Player presumed dead.]]
"The Stingray" is a malware-type entity residing in the [[Phenomenon_2|BACK-NET]], which infects any video game that can be accessed or downloaded through the network.

Infected games use a "bait-and-switch" method when played. In the first seconds to minutes of playing, everything will seem normal to the wanderer. After a certain time, it will close itself and open a maze game. 

The game seems to be made in the style of retro 3D games, having grey walls and a pitch-black floor. After a while of exploring, one will find a completely red corridor, and a 22-second timer will start, along with an incredibly distorted version of [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0Wi8Fv0AJA4 Jeopardy thinking music]. 

There is no confirmed instance of a successful playthrough, as when the 22 seconds pass, the entity is described to find the individual, no matter where they are, and kill them. If one refuses to play, the timer will automatically start.

When the entity kills the wanderer, the screen of the device they played on will change to a text saying "FOUND YOU !" along with the entity's distorted face.

== Behaviour ==
The Entity's behavior is described as unusual, as any interaction with it, while not being its target, will not result in hostility. The only way to trigger the entity is by playing its game.

While the Stingray knows the exact location of every wanderer, it chooses to use that ability on only its targets. It seems to know escape from every level, its source of information being rumored to be BACK-NET itself. The technique it uses in levels with no exits is unknown, but it is theorized to just no-clip to another level.

Despite thousands of attempts to find the physical version of the entity's habitat, its location remains unknown. It was rumored that it could hide within [[The Void]], but the most likely, yet still theorized observation says it simply doesn't exist until called to hunt by the infested game.

== Biology ==
[[File:Thestingrayphysical.jpg|thumb|227x227px|The only publicly available image of The Stingray in it's physical form. Photographer presumed dead.]]
The physical appearance of the entity is described as a humanoid with unnaturally long limbs, achieving high-level speeds when running, while the face itself seems highly distorted, almost resembling a human face. 

The whole entity is black and white, and seems unfazed by lighting, making it look unnatural and/or edited when recorded.

== Incidents ==
=== - The Big Target of 2010 ===
On February 26th, 2010, the entity was first documented. It seemed to mentally access the knowledge of anyone who played beforehand to target any wanderers who played video games before its existence, leading to more than ten thousand deaths by the end of the month.

The entity was rumored to know its targets from its creation. It is theorized that it was created for a long time, yet its knowledge and point in existence were already set.

=== - The Tests ===
After February 2010, the M.E.G. had announced a huge supply in exchange for further information about the entity, along with proof. An anonymous group decided to take random individuals hostage for testing purposes, nearly all of them dying in the process. 

While this had led to a lot of info about the entity, the M.E.G. made another announcement in 2011 that they would no longer reward such unethical tests.

